## 4. REACT/TYPESCRIPT IMPLEMENTATION RULES

### 4.1 Component Generation Standards

**File Structure:**
```
src/
├── components/
│   └── ui/                    # Match existing folder name
│       └── ComponentName/     # PascalCase folder
│           ├── index.ts       # Re-exports
│           ├── ComponentName.tsx
│           ├── ComponentName.types.ts    # If separate types used
│           ├── ComponentName.module.css  # If CSS modules
│           ├── ComponentName.stories.tsx # If Storybook exists
│           └── ComponentName.test.tsx    # If testing exists
```

**TypeScript Requirements:**
- **Strict type safety** - no `any` types unless explicitly in existing codebase
- **Forward refs** for all interactive components
- **Polymorphic components** using `as` prop if pattern exists
- **Variant props** using existing CVA/class-variance-authority or similar
- **HTML attribute extension** - extend native element interfaces properly

**Implementation Template:**
```typescript
import * as React from \'react\';
import { cn } from \'@/lib/utils\';  // Use existing utility
import { cva, type VariantProps } from \'class-variance-authority\';  // Or existing variant system

// Use existing design tokens
import { tokens } from \'@/styles/tokens\';  // Or existing token import path

const componentVariants = cva(
  \'base-classes-from-figma\',
  {
    variants: {
      variant: {
        default: \'bg-primary text-primary-foreground\',
        secondary: \'bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground\',
        // Map Figma variants exactly
      },
      size: {
        default: \'h-10 px-4 py-2\',
        sm: \'h-9 px-3\',
        lg: \'h-11 px-8\',
      },
    },
    defaultVariants: {
      variant: \'default\',
      size: \'default\',
    },
  }
);

export interface ComponentNameProps
  extends React.HTMLAttributes<HTMLDivElement>,
    VariantProps<typeof componentVariants> {
  asChild?: boolean;
  // Additional props from Figma analysis
}

const ComponentName = React.forwardRef<HTMLDivElement, ComponentNameProps>(
  ({ className, variant, size, asChild = false, ...props }, ref) => {
    // Implementation matching Figma specs exactly
    return (
      <div
        className={cn(componentVariants({ variant, size, className }))}
        ref={ref}
        {...props}
      />
    );
  }
);

ComponentName.displayName = \'ComponentName\';

export { ComponentName, componentVariants };
```

### 4.2 Styling Implementation

**Tailwind CSS (if used):**
- **Use design token mapping** - map Figma variables to Tailwind config values
- **Avoid arbitrary values** - use standard spacing scale (e.g., `p-4` not `p-[16px]`)
- **Use CSS variables** from design tokens: `bg-[var(--color-primary)]` → map to `bg-primary`
- **Responsive prefixes** - match Figma breakpoint frames (sm:, md:, lg:, xl:)

**CSS Modules (if used):**
- **Kebab-case class names** matching Figma layer names
- **CSS custom properties** for all design tokens
- **Composition patterns** matching existing component CSS

**Styled Components (if used):**
- **Theme provider integration** - use existing theme object structure
- **Prop-based styling** - match Figma variant properties

### 4.3 Asset Handling

**Images/Icons:**
- **Use existing icon system** - Lucide, Heroicons, or custom icon components
- **SVG optimization** - use existing SVGR configuration or sprite sheets
- **Image component** - use Next.js Image or existing optimized image component
- **Placeholder strategy** - use existing placeholder patterns during development

