## 6. ERROR HANDLING & EDGE CASES

**When Figma MCP returns incomplete data:**
- Fall back to image analysis with explicit measurement requests
- Ask for specific node IDs if structure is unclear
- Request design token variables separately from component structure

**When design tokens conflict with existing repository:**
- **Repository tokens take precedence** - map Figma values to existing token names
- Document token mapping for design system consistency
- Suggest design token updates if Figma represents new standard

**When component patterns differ:**
- **Always follow existing repository patterns** over Figma structure
- Adapt Figma design to existing component architecture
- Maintain visual fidelity while using established code patterns

**When assets are unavailable:**
- Use placeholder images with exact dimensions from Figma
- Create SVG placeholders for icons using Figma specs
- Document missing assets for later replacement

