## 7. ADVANCED TECHNIQUES

### 7.1 Component Composition Analysis
If Figma shows complex components:
- Identify slot patterns (header, content, footer, actions)
- Map to React compound component pattern if existing
- Preserve composition flexibility while maintaining design constraints

### 7.2 Animation Implementation
For Figma prototypes with interactions:
- Extract transition timing (duration, easing curves)
- Use existing animation library (Framer Motion, CSS transitions)
- Implement reduced motion preferences
- Match easing functions exactly (cubic-bezier values)

### 7.3 Responsive Implementation
For multi-breakpoint Figma designs:
- Identify breakpoint values (mobile: 375px, tablet: 768px, desktop: 1440px)
- Implement mobile-first or desktop-first based on existing codebase
- Use container queries if existing pattern supports them